00:31:21,560 --> 00:31:22,440
Civilian.

1132
00:31:23,520 --> 00:31:24,560
Civilian.

1133
00:31:24,560 --> 00:31:24,980
(Civilian)

1134
00:31:24,980 --> 00:31:27,300
(Glutton Ghost)

1135
00:31:27,600 --> 00:31:29,160
What?

1136
00:31:30,760 --> 00:31:32,320
We might end up looking really foolish.

1137
00:31:32,920 --> 00:31:34,240
Think carefully.

1138
00:31:34,760 --> 00:31:35,920
There's only one possibility.

1139
00:31:35,920 --> 00:31:37,520
(So you know there's only one answer)
The only way we'd look this foolish.

1140
00:31:38,280 --> 00:31:39,120
It's me.

1141
00:31:39,400 --> 00:31:40,560
Should the three of us just leave?

1142
00:31:40,560 --> 00:31:42,560
We were completely outplayed.

1143
00:31:42,560 --> 00:31:43,320
We really were.

1144
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:44,800
Exactly.

1145
00:31:44,800 --> 00:31:46,520
But I can't leave.

1146
00:31:49,600 --> 00:31:50,480
Because I'm the...

1147
00:31:51,140 --> 00:31:52,980
(Helper Ghost)

1148
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:54,600
To put it bluntly.

1149
00:31:55,180 --> 00:31:56,860
(A sense of betrayal rises)

1150
00:31:58,440 --> 00:31:59,440
One point. We got it.

1151
00:32:00,040 --> 00:32:01,040
Point secured.

1152
00:32:01,320 --> 00:32:02,320
The Glutton Ghost wins.

1153
00:32:02,880 --> 00:32:03,500
(Jin Jing +1, Zhou Keyu +1)

1154
00:32:03,500 --> 00:32:05,000
Both Glutton and Helper Ghost
get 1 point.

1155
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:06,240
Nice. It's fun.

1156
00:32:06,240 --> 00:32:07,360
That was fun.

1157
00:32:09,280 --> 00:32:10,920
So you really were Player No. 1?

1158
00:32:10,920 --> 00:32:12,320
I was.

1159
00:32:12,320 --> 00:32:13,520
He was the Helper Ghost. No choice.

1160
00:32:13,520 --> 00:32:14,120
Exactly.

1161
00:32:14,120 --> 00:32:15,920
From Helper Ghost's perspective,
he had to back me up.

1162
00:32:15,920 --> 00:32:16,600
That's right.

1163
00:32:16,600 --> 00:32:17,760
But I got lucky this round.

1164
00:32:17,760 --> 00:32:19,080
Seats No. 3 and No. 4 were empty,

1165
00:32:19,080 --> 00:32:20,400
which created a lot of possible scenarios.

1166
00:32:20,620 --> 00:32:21,380
(That really worked in your favor)

1167
00:32:21,560 --> 00:32:23,400
Then why didn't you suspect her?

1168
00:32:24,120 --> 00:32:24,680
I did.

1169
00:32:24,680 --> 00:32:26,240
I mentioned that possibility.

1170
00:32:26,240 --> 00:32:27,040
I thought it was unlikely.

1171
00:32:27,520 --> 00:32:28,760
(No avoiding it this time)
Why unlikely?

1172
00:32:28,960 --> 00:32:29,800
It wasn't unlikely at all.

1173
00:32:29,800 --> 00:32:31,200
It was very likely. It was her.

1174
00:32:31,520 --> 00:32:33,640
All I remember is someone saying,

1175
00:32:33,640 --> 00:32:34,840
Jin Jing, choose carefully.

1176
00:32:34,840 --> 00:32:36,360
But if you're actually the villain,

1177
00:32:36,360 --> 00:32:37,440
I'll end up looking like a fool.

1178
00:32:37,440 --> 00:32:38,480
(He'll never live that line down)
I remember that.

1179
00:32:39,240 --> 00:32:39,560
Exactly.

1180
00:32:39,960 --> 00:32:41,160
I almost burst out laughing.

1181
00:32:42,480 --> 00:32:43,600
You let a villain decide in the end.

1182
00:32:43,880 --> 00:32:44,680
I honestly never

1183
00:32:44,680 --> 00:32:46,160
expected him to be the Helper Ghost.

1184
00:32:48,160 --> 00:32:48,920
Alright.

1185
00:32:48,920 --> 00:32:49,920
I'll deal the cards this time.

1186
00:32:49,920 --> 00:32:52,370
(Drawing identities)

1187
00:32:52,400 --> 00:32:53,200
Not yours yet.

1188
00:32:53,720 --> 00:32:54,800
You'll get the last card.

1189
00:32:56,500 --> 00:32:57,540
(Getting into character before starting)

1190
00:33:11,320 --> 00:33:11,800
Close your eyes.

1191
00:33:12,760 --> 00:33:13,800
Night falls. Close your eyes.

1192
00:33:13,980 --> 00:33:16,420
(Glutton bug fix, Round 2)

1193
00:33:16,440 --> 00:33:17,440
Player No. 1, open your eyes.

1194
00:33:18,580 --> 00:33:20,220
(Seat No. 1 is empty)

1195
00:33:21,780 --> 00:33:24,020
(Listening carefully for any sound)

1196
00:33:33,320 --> 00:33:33,760
Choked again?

1197
00:33:33,760 --> 00:33:34,800
They choked while eating.

1198
00:33:35,260 --> 00:33:36,780
(Possible bug detected)

1199
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:38,040
They choked on it again.

1200
00:33:38,720 --> 00:33:39,760
Player No. 1, close your eyes.

1201
00:33:40,960 --> 00:33:42,000
Player No. 2, open your eyes.

1202
00:33:47,140 --> 00:33:52,020
(Player No. 2 this round)

1203
00:33:55,500 --> 00:33:57,620
(What?)

1204
00:33:59,220 --> 00:34:00,740
(No way)

1205
00:34:01,180 --> 00:34:02,700
(Not me)

1206
00:34:03,500 --> 00:34:04,200
(That was close.
I almost became Helper Ghost)

1207
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:05,160
What was that sound?

1208
00:34:05,840 --> 00:34:06,440
So much movement?

1209
00:34:06,680 --> 00:34:07,520
Are they still eating?

1210
00:34:08,120 --> 00:34:08,760
Taking forever.

1211
00:34:14,040 --> 00:34:15,230
Who's chewing?

1212
00:34:15,230 --> 00:34:16,400
Player No. 2, close your eyes.

1213
00:34:18,040 --> 00:34:19,120
Player No. 3, open your eyes.

1214
00:34:21,180 --> 00:34:24,140
(Seat No. 3 is empty)

1215
00:34:25,040 --> 00:34:27,080
What? Is someone eating?

1216
00:34:28,100 --> 00:34:31,340
(Pretending to chew)

1217
00:34:33,620 --> 00:34:36,300
(Trying to identify the sound)

1218
00:34:37,480 --> 00:34:38,560
Player No. 3, close your eyes.

1219
00:34:39,600 --> 00:34:40,710
Player No. 4, open your eyes.

1220
00:34:43,060 --> 00:34:47,700
(Player No. 4 this round)

1221
00:34:48,230 --> 00:34:49,320
What does that mean?

1222
00:34:51,260 --> 00:34:52,980
(Huh?)

1223
00:34:57,780 --> 00:34:58,980
(Glutton Ghost: Zhang Linghe.
Helper Ghost to be chosen)

1224
00:34:59,000 --> 00:34:59,840
Who's laughing?

1225
00:35:05,520 --> 00:35:05,920
No.

1226
00:35:05,920 --> 00:35:07,760
Why is everyone smacking their lips?

1227
00:35:09,020 --> 00:35:11,260
(Trying hard to swallow)

1228
00:35:11,260 --> 00:35:15,020
(The sourness kicks in)

1229
00:35:15,540 --> 00:35:17,340
(Drawing attention)

1230
00:35:17,960 --> 00:35:18,880
Too spicy?

1231
00:35:18,880 --> 00:35:19,440
Hold on.

1232
00:35:19,440 --> 00:35:20,680
(Successfully draws attention)
I'm voting you out.

1233
00:35:20,680 --> 00:35:22,100
(Seriously)

1234
00:35:22,160 --> 00:35:23,080
He's overacting.

1235
00:35:24,760 --> 00:35:26,120
I'm voting for you first.

1236
00:35:30,060 --> 00:35:31,340
(Finally swallows it)

1237
00:35:32,240 --> 00:35:33,000
It's stuck in my teeth.

1238
00:35:33,180 --> 00:35:35,220
(Committed to the performance
until the very end)

1239
00:35:35,240 --> 00:35:36,320
Player No. 4, close your eyes.

1240
00:35:36,320 --> 00:35:37,440
Player No. 5, open your eyes.

1241
00:35:38,620 --> 00:35:41,940
(Seat No. 5 is empty)

1242
00:35:41,940 --> 00:35:43,300
(Still staying in character)

1243
00:35:45,600 --> 00:35:46,720
Stop spitting it out, Ding.

1244
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:48,720
That wasn't easy.

1245
00:35:48,720 --> 00:35:49,800
Player No. 5, close your eyes.

1246
00:35:50,160 --> 00:35:51,440
Glutton Ghost, open your eyes.

1247
00:35:53,040 --> 00:35:55,120
Glutton Ghost, please choose one player
to be Helper Ghost.

1248
00:35:59,380 --> 00:36:02,660
(Helper Ghost)

1249
00:36:03,880 --> 00:36:05,480
What do you mean, he went around?

1250
00:36:05,480 --> 00:36:06,440
He's still running?

1251
00:36:06,440 --> 00:36:06,800
No.

1252
00:36:06,800 --> 00:36:07,400
He...

1253
00:36:07,400 --> 00:36:08,640
(Glutton Ghost He, Helper Ghost Ding)
He couldn't point to that person.

1254
00:36:08,640 --> 00:36:10,400
So he had to go tap him.

1255
00:36:10,400 --> 00:36:11,840
(He really couldn't reach)

1256
00:36:11,840 --> 00:36:13,040
He couldn't point to him.

1257
00:36:13,600 --> 00:36:15,360
Helper Ghost, open your eyes
and identify each other.

1258
00:36:15,580 --> 00:36:18,100
(Electro Kids, round two)

1259
00:36:23,760 --> 00:36:25,400
(Whoever makes a sound gets suspected)
That sigh, Ke.

1260
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:26,800
Ke.

1261
00:36:26,960 --> 00:36:28,360
(Whoever it is, pile on right away)
So it was you.

1262
00:36:29,280 --> 00:36:32,240
Don't use that outside stuff, okay?

1263
00:36:32,240 --> 00:36:33,540
(She's suspecting everything now)

1264
00:36:33,840 --> 00:36:35,320
Daybreak. Open your eyes.

1265
00:36:35,880 --> 00:36:36,720
I can finally open my eyes.

1266
00:36:37,160 --> 00:36:38,040
I almost fell asleep.

1267
00:36:39,560 --> 00:36:40,920
Who ate all the peel?

1268
00:36:41,300 --> 00:36:43,780
(Speaking first
to claim a good-guy spot)

1269
00:36:44,320 --> 00:36:45,760
Eating the peel?

1270
00:36:45,980 --> 00:36:48,060
(Bro's appetite is no joke)

1271
00:36:48,400 --> 00:36:50,120
Come on. Let's draw numbers
to speak, okay?

1272
00:36:50,120 --> 00:36:51,200
Draw numbers to speak.

1273
00:36:51,800 --> 00:36:53,080
(For fairness)
Lowest number speaks first.

1274
00:36:53,080 --> 00:36:53,840
(Rule upgrade: draw numbers to speak)

1275
00:36:53,840 --> 00:36:54,720
I'm three.

1276
00:36:54,720 --> 00:36:55,520
I'm one.

1277
00:36:55,520 --> 00:36:56,080
Two.

1278
00:36:56,320 --> 00:36:56,600
Five.

1279
00:36:57,640 --> 00:36:57,880
Two.

1280
00:36:58,560 --> 00:37:00,080
(Same number 2)
What do we do if they're the same?

1281
00:37:00,080 --> 00:37:02,120
We'll play rock, paper,
scissors for two and three.

1282
00:37:02,120 --> 00:37:02,520
Okay, come on.

1283
00:37:02,520 --> 00:37:03,440
Winner gets three.

1284
00:37:03,440 --> 00:37:04,360
Rock, paper, scissors.

1285
00:37:04,360 --> 00:37:05,460
(No. 2 Jin Jing, No. 3 Zhou Keyu)

1286
00:37:05,460 --> 00:37:06,300
(Speaking order this round:
No. 1 Zhang Linghe)

1287
00:37:06,300 --> 00:37:06,500
(No. 2 Jin Jing)

1288
00:37:06,500 --> 00:37:07,500
(No. 3 Zhou Keyu)

1289
00:37:07,500 --> 00:37:08,740
(No. 4 Liu Yuning)

1290
00:37:08,740 --> 00:37:09,280
(No. 5 Ding Chengxin)

1291
00:37:09,280 --> 00:37:10,200
Okay, good.

1292
00:37:10,200 --> 00:37:10,960
I'm No. 4.

1293
00:37:10,960 --> 00:37:11,600
(No. 1's speaking time)

1294
00:37:11,600 --> 00:37:12,400
When I opened my eyes,

1295
00:37:12,400 --> 00:37:13,440
this was all still whole.

1296
00:37:13,440 --> 00:37:14,040
No one had eaten it.

1297
00:37:14,580 --> 00:37:15,580
(Then it can only be)

1298
00:37:15,580 --> 00:37:16,500
(You)

1299
00:37:16,500 --> 00:37:18,820
(Using this move again, He?)

1300
00:37:19,080 --> 00:37:21,200
But while I was opening my eyes,

1301
00:37:21,200 --> 00:37:22,040
no one else opened theirs.

1302
00:37:22,760 --> 00:37:23,360
I'm No. 4.

1303
00:37:23,360 --> 00:37:24,440
No one is No. 4.

1304
00:37:24,500 --> 00:37:25,140
(Got it?)

1305
00:37:25,900 --> 00:37:27,820
(Ready to get piled on)

1306
00:37:28,860 --> 00:37:31,500
(Successfully became suspicious)

1307
00:37:31,520 --> 00:37:32,240
So...

1308
00:37:32,240 --> 00:37:34,680
In that case, No. 2 speaks.

1309
00:37:34,680 --> 00:37:35,280
No. 2 speaks.

1310
00:37:35,280 --> 00:37:35,920
(No. 2's speaking time)
I'm No. 2.

1311
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:36,400
Okay.

1312
00:37:36,800 --> 00:37:37,440
When I opened my eyes,

1313
00:37:37,440 --> 00:37:38,840
the lemons were still there.

1314
00:37:38,840 --> 00:37:40,360
(Playing dumb)

1315
00:37:40,360 --> 00:37:42,040
Someone opened their eyes
at the same time as me.

1316
00:37:43,160 --> 00:37:44,520
Three people opened
their eyes together.

1317
00:37:45,600 --> 00:37:46,840
Three people opened
their eyes together?

1318
00:37:46,840 --> 00:37:47,400
Yes.

1319
00:37:47,400 --> 00:37:51,060
(Did I hear that right?)

1320
00:37:52,800 --> 00:37:53,900
Three people?

1321
00:37:53,900 --> 00:37:55,560
(You mean everyone except us two?)

1322
00:37:55,560 --> 00:37:56,360
When I opened my eyes,

1323
00:37:56,360 --> 00:37:57,520
I just felt like

1324
00:37:57,960 --> 00:38:00,240
the Glutton Ghost
is pretty screwed this round.

1325
00:38:00,720 --> 00:38:01,760
Three people?

1326
00:38:05,040 --> 00:38:06,720
Three people opened their eyes together?

1327
00:38:07,140 --> 00:38:09,220
(There are only five people total)

1328
00:38:09,240 --> 00:38:10,840
(I really can't believe this)
No, who are the three?

1329
00:38:10,840 --> 00:38:11,720
Anyway, I'm not you (round one).

1330
00:38:11,720 --> 00:38:12,560
She didn't say.

1331
00:38:12,560 --> 00:38:13,880
(I know you're anxious, but calm down)
Why do you care who they are?

1332
00:38:14,600 --> 00:38:15,320
You're getting nervous.

1333
00:38:16,040 --> 00:38:16,880
You're getting nervous.

1334
00:38:17,100 --> 00:38:18,820
(Calm down, He)

1335
00:38:18,840 --> 00:38:20,560
Ning, Ke, Jin.

1336
00:38:21,280 --> 00:38:22,240
You three.

1337
00:38:22,240 --> 00:38:23,960
(Checking again and again)
Then the two of us are later.

1338
00:38:23,960 --> 00:38:25,640
According to your testimony.

1339
00:38:26,280 --> 00:38:27,840
You two were in other positions.

1340
00:38:27,840 --> 00:38:28,960
I can't say you were later.

1341
00:38:29,880 --> 00:38:31,280
Then it's one of them, right?

1342
00:38:31,280 --> 00:38:31,800
Right.

1343
00:38:31,800 --> 00:38:34,300
(The situation is looking really bad)

1344
00:38:34,320 --> 00:38:36,040
No, how could three people
open their eyes together?

1345
00:38:36,040 --> 00:38:36,440
That's so...

1346
00:38:38,600 --> 00:38:39,600
This round is kind of hard.

1347
00:38:39,600 --> 00:38:40,320
It really is.

1348
00:38:40,320 --> 00:38:41,440
This round really is.

1349
00:38:41,440 --> 00:38:42,160
Dear viewers,

1350
00:38:42,160 --> 00:38:43,670
(That's the situation)
this round is

1351
00:38:43,680 --> 00:38:45,000
really rough for the Glutton Ghost.

1352
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:45,920
(Disaster from the start)

1353
00:38:45,920 --> 00:38:47,520
I opened my eyes on the second night.

1354
00:38:48,200 --> 00:38:50,280
(No. 3's turn)
I opened my eyes with Jin and Ning.

1355
00:38:50,280 --> 00:38:51,480
Then on the second night,

1356
00:38:51,480 --> 00:38:52,520
nothing happened.

1357
00:38:52,520 --> 00:38:53,720
No one ate the lemon.

1358
00:38:53,720 --> 00:38:54,720
As everyone knows,

1359
00:38:54,720 --> 00:38:56,840
a triangle is very stable.

1360
00:38:56,840 --> 00:38:58,760
So right now, we're an iron triangle,

1361
00:38:58,760 --> 00:38:59,120
right?

1362
00:38:59,120 --> 00:38:59,560
Right.

1363
00:38:59,560 --> 00:39:00,480
Even if one of us

1364
00:39:00,480 --> 00:39:01,760
(Iron triangle of three obtuse angles)
is the Helper Ghost,

1365
00:39:01,760 --> 00:39:02,640
(Doesn't dare make any expression)
it still means

1366
00:39:02,640 --> 00:39:03,920
we don't need to worry
about that person.

1367
00:39:03,920 --> 00:39:04,840
So,

1368
00:39:04,840 --> 00:39:06,320
whether or not one of the three of us

1369
00:39:06,320 --> 00:39:07,800
is the Helper Ghost,

1370
00:39:08,520 --> 00:39:09,600
the Glutton Ghost

1371
00:39:09,600 --> 00:39:11,680
has to be either He or Ding.

1372
00:39:14,080 --> 00:39:15,160
So the good guys this round

1373
00:39:15,160 --> 00:39:16,760
just need to vote with us
against these two.

1374
00:39:16,760 --> 00:39:19,040
Right now, He is claiming

1375
00:39:19,040 --> 00:39:20,320
he opened his eyes on night four.

1376
00:39:20,320 --> 00:39:21,440
No one ate the lemon.

1377
00:39:23,000 --> 00:39:23,840
So for you,

1378
00:39:23,840 --> 00:39:24,960
it should be very clear.

1379
00:39:24,960 --> 00:39:25,280
You don't even need to listen.

1380
00:39:25,280 --> 00:39:25,920
I'm very clear.

1381
00:39:27,400 --> 00:39:29,200
Okay, then. Alright.

1382
00:39:30,540 --> 00:39:32,260
(You just trust me like that?)

1383
00:39:32,260 --> 00:39:34,740
(Pressure's on)

1384
00:39:35,360 --> 00:39:36,880
Let's see how you save this.

1385
00:39:36,880 --> 00:39:39,120
Let's see how you
turn this around, Ding.

1386
00:39:39,120 --> 00:39:40,040
Which number were you?

1387
00:39:40,560 --> 00:39:41,640
Which number was I?

1388
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:44,560
Was I one or five?

1389
00:39:44,560 --> 00:39:45,200
I forgot.

1390
00:39:45,840 --> 00:39:48,440
One or five? You forgot?

1391
00:39:49,400 --> 00:39:50,880
How could you forget?

1392
00:39:50,880 --> 00:39:52,540
(Let's see your show)

1393
00:39:52,540 --> 00:39:53,740
(A lying show)

1394
00:39:53,740 --> 00:39:54,960
(Unconscious little move, shifty eyes)

1395
00:39:54,960 --> 00:39:56,760
Trying to muddy the water like this

1396
00:39:57,200 --> 00:39:58,880
isn't a good look, Ding.

1397
00:39:58,880 --> 00:39:59,280
How about this?

1398
00:39:59,280 --> 00:40:00,600
I'll say something for you, okay?

1399
00:40:00,600 --> 00:40:01,680
Could it be him?

1400
00:40:01,680 --> 00:40:02,880
Maybe he's actually the Glutton.

1401
00:40:02,880 --> 00:40:04,920
He picked him as the Helper.

1402
00:40:04,920 --> 00:40:06,400
So now he's pushing him out

1403
00:40:06,400 --> 00:40:07,400
as the Glutton.

1404
00:40:07,400 --> 00:40:09,140
(He's been read)

1405
00:40:09,180 --> 00:40:09,960
(Is she a prophet?)

1406
00:40:09,960 --> 00:40:10,400
Is that it?

1407
00:40:10,400 --> 00:40:11,320
Did that help a bit?

1408
00:40:11,700 --> 00:40:13,120
(That was acting.
Now he's really nervous)

1409
00:40:13,120 --> 00:40:14,240
Let him speak for himself.

1410
00:40:16,100 --> 00:40:18,380
(Bring out our Electro Kid spirit)

1411
00:40:18,520 --> 00:40:19,840
Which round were you, Ding?

1412
00:40:20,480 --> 00:40:21,440
Which round was I?

1413
00:40:21,440 --> 00:40:22,360
I was round five.

1414
00:40:22,580 --> 00:40:24,860
(Pretending to hesitate)

1415
00:40:26,560 --> 00:40:27,840
Then we're done.

1416
00:40:28,140 --> 00:40:30,420
(Let the suspicion hit harder)

1417
00:40:30,440 --> 00:40:31,640
Then did you eat it in round five?

1418
00:40:31,640 --> 00:40:32,600
(Judging again from
the "good guy" high ground)

1419
00:40:32,600 --> 00:40:33,960
Did the person before you eat it?

1420
00:40:33,980 --> 00:40:36,940
(Ate it, didn't eat it)

1421
00:40:38,440 --> 00:40:39,200
He's thinking.

1422
00:40:39,200 --> 00:40:40,560
When you opened your eyes,
was there still lemon?

1423
00:40:41,320 --> 00:40:42,280
When I opened my eyes,

1424
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:44,160
there was no lemon left.

1425
00:40:44,680 --> 00:40:45,680
Then it was four.

1426
00:40:45,680 --> 00:40:47,000
(Got them fighting each other)

1427
00:40:47,000 --> 00:40:48,160
One says five ate it.

1428
00:40:48,160 --> 00:40:49,120
One says four ate it.

1429
00:40:49,560 --> 00:40:50,640
And let me tell you.

1430
00:40:50,640 --> 00:40:51,480
Close-up right here.

1431
00:40:51,480 --> 00:40:53,240
Look how innocent his eyes are.

1432
00:40:53,820 --> 00:40:54,840
(Baby-like innocent eyes)

1433
00:40:54,840 --> 00:40:55,560
So innocent.

1434
00:40:56,240 --> 00:40:56,520
What?

1435
00:40:56,520 --> 00:40:57,040
Then I get it.

1436
00:40:57,040 --> 00:40:59,440
What? Like he hasn't fooled us before?

1437
00:41:00,440 --> 00:41:01,800
I'm on the Electroshock team.

1438
00:41:02,300 --> 00:41:03,860
(Danger)

1439
00:41:03,880 --> 00:41:05,080
No, because he spoke first.

1440
00:41:05,080 --> 00:41:06,780
(Speaking up for him)
So he looks slightly better.

1441
00:41:07,040 --> 00:41:07,680
Vote.

1442
00:41:07,680 --> 00:41:08,600
(No more delays. Lock it in fast)

1443
00:41:08,600 --> 00:41:10,760
Any more speeches? Anyone?

1444
00:41:10,760 --> 00:41:11,920
What else is there to say?

1445
00:41:12,240 --> 00:41:13,400
I'm done.

1446
00:41:13,400 --> 00:41:14,240
(Pretending he exposed himself)

1447
00:41:14,240 --> 00:41:14,960
Then there's nothing you can do.

1448
00:41:14,960 --> 00:41:16,320
I can't do anything now.

1449
00:41:16,320 --> 00:41:17,720
Disaster start, Ding.

1450
00:41:18,560 --> 00:41:19,160
Total disaster.

1451
00:41:19,680 --> 00:41:20,600
Then let's vote.

1452
00:41:20,600 --> 00:41:22,720
It's just one, two, three, four, five.

1453
00:41:22,720 --> 00:41:23,880
I don't need to know one to five.

1454
00:41:23,880 --> 00:41:25,840
I just need to know
which number Ding is.

1455
00:41:26,420 --> 00:41:27,900
(We've got this)

1456
00:41:28,200 --> 00:41:28,760
Vote.

1457
00:41:30,060 --> 00:41:31,660
(Ding x5)

1458
00:41:31,660 --> 00:41:32,640
(Sweeps all the votes)

1459
00:41:32,640 --> 00:41:33,280
So tragic.

1460
00:41:33,760 --> 00:41:34,440
So tragic, Ding.

1461
00:41:34,440 --> 00:41:35,000
I really...

1462
00:41:35,000 --> 00:41:35,400
Ding.

1463
00:41:35,720 --> 00:41:36,640
Too tragic.

1464
00:41:37,200 --> 00:41:38,120
Nothing I can do.

1465
00:41:38,120 --> 00:41:40,480
I picked one of the three good guys.

1466
00:41:40,480 --> 00:41:41,200
(Still acting)

1467
00:41:41,200 --> 00:41:42,080
(Playing along)
Who's the Helper?

1468
00:41:42,520 --> 00:41:43,200
Who?

1469
00:41:43,200 --> 00:41:43,680
Ning?

1470
00:41:43,680 --> 00:41:44,600
Probably Ning.

1471
00:41:44,600 --> 00:41:45,600
No, it's not me.

1472
00:41:45,600 --> 00:41:46,480
(The iron triangle collapses)

1473
00:41:46,480 --> 00:41:47,280
It's you.

1474
00:41:47,280 --> 00:41:48,640
You're still acting.

1475
00:41:49,200 --> 00:41:49,520
You don't wanna admit it.

1476
00:41:49,520 --> 00:41:50,360
Stop acting.

1477
00:41:50,760 --> 00:41:51,720
You don't wanna admit it.

1478
00:41:52,360 --> 00:41:53,320
Nothing I can do.

1479
00:41:55,060 --> 00:41:56,020
(Blank board)

1480
00:41:59,960 --> 00:42:00,880
Am I a blank board?

1481
00:42:00,880 --> 00:42:01,240
Wait.

1482
00:42:01,240 --> 00:42:02,160
(The act must go on)
Let me wipe it.

1483
00:42:02,160 --> 00:42:03,480
You're that good?

1484
00:42:03,480 --> 00:42:05,720
You're already that amazing now?

1485
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:06,880
What?

1486
00:42:07,080 --> 00:42:08,040
He Jiahuan,

1487
00:42:08,040 --> 00:42:10,680
(Basic move)
have you gotten so advanced

1488
00:42:10,680 --> 00:42:12,920
that you made up something
I just happened not to know?

1489
00:42:14,680 --> 00:42:15,760
He's the Glutton.

1490
00:42:15,760 --> 00:42:16,920
He's the Helper.

1491
00:42:16,920 --> 00:42:17,900
(It finally clicks)

1492
00:42:17,900 --> 00:42:19,460
(The Electro Kids team up
perfectly again)

1493
00:42:20,560 --> 00:42:22,640
Don't be fooled by appearances.

1494
00:42:22,960 --> 00:42:24,440
I said it earlier.

1495
00:42:24,440 --> 00:42:26,760
Like he hasn't fooled us before?

1496
00:42:27,800 --> 00:42:28,520
Good thing I

1497
00:42:28,520 --> 00:42:29,880
brought up another theory earlier.

1498
00:42:30,840 --> 00:42:32,240
Makes me look a little less dumb.

1499
00:42:32,240 --> 00:42:33,820
(Dumb)

1500
00:42:36,440 --> 00:42:37,080
You know,

1501
00:42:37,080 --> 00:42:38,080
I've been thinking,

1502
00:42:38,080 --> 00:42:39,080
how should I claim?

1503
00:42:39,080 --> 00:42:39,920
What should I say

1504
00:42:39,920 --> 00:42:41,080
to pull it back a bit?

1505
00:42:41,080 --> 00:42:41,920
It's so hard.

1506
00:42:41,920 --> 00:42:43,640
When all three of them
claim the same number,

1507
00:42:43,640 --> 00:42:44,600
there's only one play.

1508
00:42:44,600 --> 00:42:45,040
Yeah.

1509
00:42:45,040 --> 00:42:46,280
(Electro Kids' signals sync perfectly)
Vote you out.

1510
00:42:46,280 --> 00:42:46,600
Yeah.

1511
00:42:46,600 --> 00:42:47,720
I knew they'd vote me.

1512
00:42:47,720 --> 00:42:48,960
But what could I say

1513
00:42:49,520 --> 00:42:51,200
to make it look
like I was exposing myself?

1514
00:42:51,720 --> 00:42:53,080
To pull things back a little.

1515
00:42:53,520 --> 00:42:54,640
In the middle of total disaster,

1516
00:42:54,640 --> 00:42:56,480
there was a bit of a dream hand, right?

1517
00:42:57,120 --> 00:42:57,840
That works.

1518
00:42:57,840 --> 00:42:59,560
We had a fifty-fifty shot,
and we picked wrong.

1519
00:42:59,560 --> 00:42:59,880
Okay.

1520
00:43:00,400 --> 00:43:01,800
The Glutton Ghost wins.

1521
00:43:01,800 --> 00:43:03,920
The Glutton Ghost
and Helper Ghost get one point.

1522
00:43:03,920 --> 00:43:04,640
(The Electro Kids score again)

1523
00:43:04,640 --> 00:43:05,520
One point each.

1524
00:43:05,880 --> 00:43:07,040
Congrats.

1525
00:43:07,040 --> 00:43:07,880
(Current score)
Nice.

1526
00:43:07,880 --> 00:43:08,760
Let's play another round.

1527
00:43:09,200 --> 00:43:10,040
Let's switch the food.

1528
00:43:10,040 --> 00:43:11,080
Pistachios?

1529
00:43:11,080 --> 00:43:12,840
The kind that makes noise
when you eat it.

1530
00:43:13,680 --> 00:43:15,120
You can swallow it like medicine.

1531
00:43:15,920 --> 00:43:16,240
Yeah.

1532
00:43:17,560 --> 00:43:18,880
Let's go hardcore.

1533
00:43:18,880 --> 00:43:20,060
(Truly hardcore)
Swallow it with the shell.

1534
00:43:20,060 --> 00:43:23,020
(Drawing identities)

1535
00:43:23,020 --> 00:43:24,060
(Still acting)

1536
00:43:24,100 --> 00:43:24,620
(Cut)

1537
00:43:28,640 --> 00:43:29,440
Draw numbers.

1538
00:43:29,460 --> 00:43:33,460
(Drawing wake-up numbers)

1539
00:43:33,680 --> 00:43:34,800
Night falls. Close your eyes.

1540
00:43:34,800 --> 00:43:35,880
(Glutton bug fix, Round 3)

1541
00:43:35,880 --> 00:43:36,800
No. 1, open your eyes.

1542
00:43:37,580 --> 00:43:38,940
(This round's No. 1)

1543
00:43:39,320 --> 00:43:40,920
No.1,

1544
00:43:41,560 --> 00:43:42,560
say something.

1545
00:43:42,560 --> 00:43:43,780
(No. 1 stays silent)

1546
00:43:44,560 --> 00:43:45,320
Don't you know

1547
00:43:45,320 --> 00:43:46,960
we need to hear him peel the shell?

1548
00:43:47,560 --> 00:43:48,200
Right.

1549
00:43:49,240 --> 00:43:50,760
Start peeling, No. 1.

1550
00:43:51,340 --> 00:43:52,040
(Can't hold it in)

1551
00:43:52,040 --> 00:43:53,160
Lead peeler, let's go.

1552
00:43:54,340 --> 00:43:56,180
(Listening closely)

1553
00:43:58,340 --> 00:44:00,540
(Since you asked)

1554
00:44:01,000 --> 00:44:01,400
This...

1555
00:44:04,240 --> 00:44:05,520
Ning.

1556
00:44:07,260 --> 00:44:08,740
(Smack)

1557
00:44:08,960 --> 00:44:10,560
What kind of shell are you peeling?

1558
00:44:10,560 --> 00:44:11,880
You peeled your bracelet.

1559
00:44:11,880 --> 00:44:14,240
He's doing "breaking
a boulder on his chest".

1560
00:44:19,900 --> 00:44:21,820
(Mischief is contagious)

1561
00:44:21,820 --> 00:44:23,660
(Shell-cracking white noise)

1562
00:44:26,800 --> 00:44:28,040
Jin Jing, what noise are you making?

1563
00:44:29,160 --> 00:44:29,800
You heard all that.

1564
00:44:29,800 --> 00:44:31,460
Why isn't Zhou Keyu reacting?

1565
00:44:31,460 --> 00:44:33,380
(Already lulled to sleep
by the sound bowl)

1566
00:44:33,560 --> 00:44:34,680
No. 1, close your eyes.

1567
00:44:36,000 --> 00:44:37,080
No. 2, open your eyes.

1568
00:44:38,900 --> 00:44:40,940
(This round's No. 2)

1569
00:44:42,060 --> 00:44:44,540
(Current setup: Confidential,
Glutton Ghost, Confidential)

1570
00:44:44,560 --> 00:44:45,560
No. 3, open your eyes.

1571
00:44:45,560 --> 00:44:46,600
(No. 3 spot empty)

1572
00:44:46,600 --> 00:44:47,720
No. 4, open your eyes.

1573
00:44:47,720 --> 00:44:49,140
(No. 4 spot empty)

1574
00:44:49,320 --> 00:44:50,440
No. 5, open your eyes.

1575
00:44:51,420 --> 00:44:53,820
(No. 5 spot)

1576
00:44:56,780 --> 00:44:58,540
(Face working overtime)

1577
00:45:00,340 --> 00:45:01,340
(Empty)

1578
00:45:01,340 --> 00:45:04,340
(Crime scene)

1579
00:45:06,520 --> 00:45:08,040
No. 5, close your eyes.

1580
00:45:08,360 --> 00:45:09,640
Glutton Ghost, open your eyes.

1581
00:45:09,900 --> 00:45:12,380
(Glutton Ghost's pick: Confidential)

1582
00:45:12,840 --> 00:45:14,000
Day breaks. Open your eyes.

1583
00:45:14,800 --> 00:45:15,840
He fell asleep again.

1584
00:45:15,840 --> 00:45:18,900
(Glutton Ghost, Confidential,
Helper Ghost, Confidential)

1585
00:45:18,920 --> 00:45:21,840
It's very clear.

1586
00:45:22,600 --> 00:45:24,800
We're back to "very clear", Ding.

1587
00:45:26,680 --> 00:45:27,660
(Innocent)
Why?

1588
00:45:28,880 --> 00:45:30,240
I'm too clear.

1589
00:45:31,320 --> 00:45:32,040
It's fine. Let's talk.

1590
00:45:32,040 --> 00:45:32,960
Come on, draw cards.

1591
00:45:33,360 --> 00:45:34,520
What's clear now?

1592
00:45:34,520 --> 00:45:35,400
(Drawing speaking order)

1593
00:45:35,400 --> 00:45:35,800
Ding,

1594
00:45:35,800 --> 00:45:37,400
turns out No. 5 speaks.

1595
00:45:37,500 --> 00:45:39,220
(Won't respond)

1596
00:45:40,000 --> 00:45:40,800
I'm 5.

1597
00:45:40,800 --> 00:45:42,020
(No. 5 isn't smiling)

1598
00:45:42,120 --> 00:45:42,960
I...

1599
00:45:42,960 --> 00:45:44,260
(No. 1)
I drew 1 again.

1600
00:45:44,760 --> 00:45:45,280
Three.

1601
00:45:45,680 --> 00:45:46,680
Two.

1602
00:45:46,680 --> 00:45:46,960
One.

1603
00:45:46,960 --> 00:45:47,800
Let's do it.

1604
00:45:47,800 --> 00:45:49,040
Rock, paper, scissors.

1605
00:45:49,440 --> 00:45:50,360
(Paper, rock)
Okay, then I'll go later.

1606
00:45:51,000 --> 00:45:51,840
(No. 3 Zhou Keyu, No. 2 Zhang Linghe)
I'm No. 2.

1607
00:45:51,840 --> 00:45:52,360
I'm No. 3.

1608
00:45:52,360 --> 00:45:53,940
(No. 4)

1609
00:45:54,200 --> 00:45:55,120
(No. 1's speaking time)
I don't have much to say.

1610
00:45:55,120 --> 00:45:56,520
I opened my eyes first.

1611
00:45:57,560 --> 00:46:00,000
But I'm not the Glutton Ghost.

1612
00:46:00,000 --> 00:46:01,560
So I didn't eat.

1613
00:46:04,760 --> 00:46:05,240
Beautiful.

1614
00:46:05,820 --> 00:46:07,100
(No. 2's speaking time)

1615
00:46:07,120 --> 00:46:08,640
What number did I
open my eyes on again?

1616
00:46:08,960 --> 00:46:10,000
What number did we
open our eyes on again?

1617
00:46:10,020 --> 00:46:11,340
(Stays silent)

1618
00:46:12,460 --> 00:46:14,060
(Meaningful look)

1619
00:46:14,440 --> 00:46:15,120
Say it.

1620
00:46:15,120 --> 00:46:16,480
Don't stay quiet.

1621
00:46:16,480 --> 00:46:17,120
It's not my turn.

1622
00:46:17,120 --> 00:46:17,800
I can't talk.

1623
00:46:18,280 --> 00:46:19,840
What number did we
open our eyes on again?

1624
00:46:20,680 --> 00:46:21,640
No. 2.

1625
00:46:21,640 --> 00:46:22,480
No. 2, right?

1626
00:46:22,720 --> 00:46:23,600
I opened my eyes at No. 2.

1627
00:46:24,160 --> 00:46:26,360
Then three people opened
their eyes at the same time.

1628
00:46:26,800 --> 00:46:27,920
Three people at once again.

1629
00:46:27,920 --> 00:46:29,280
Three people opened their eyes together?

1630
00:46:29,640 --> 00:46:32,320
That's it.

1631
00:46:35,440 --> 00:46:36,320
One, two, three.

1632
00:46:36,800 --> 00:46:37,960
Three of us opened
our eyes together just now.

1633
00:46:37,960 --> 00:46:38,640
Did anyone eat?

1634
00:46:40,120 --> 00:46:41,640
Keep going. Get to the point.

1635
00:46:41,640 --> 00:46:42,700
(Pressuring him)
Get to the point.

1636
00:46:42,760 --> 00:46:43,760
What else?

1637
00:46:43,760 --> 00:46:44,360
Get to the point.

1638
00:46:44,360 --> 00:46:45,180
(Going head-to-head)

1639
00:46:45,700 --> 00:46:47,100
(Cheerful on his own)

1640
00:46:48,740 --> 00:46:54,820
(Everyone has their own thoughts)

1641
00:46:55,520 --> 00:46:56,520
So dramatic.

1642
00:46:56,520 --> 00:46:57,560
We're done.

1643
00:46:57,560 --> 00:46:58,480
Who even is this?

1644
00:46:59,200 --> 00:47:00,200
I wanna hear from those two.

1645
00:47:00,200 --> 00:47:00,920
I wanna hear what they say.

1646
00:47:00,920 --> 00:47:01,200
No.

1647
00:47:01,200 --> 00:47:02,120
You're No. 2.

1648
00:47:02,120 --> 00:47:03,240
(What role are you?)
And you still wanna hear from them?

1649
00:47:03,240 --> 00:47:03,680
I said it.

1650
00:47:03,680 --> 00:47:04,520
I'm done.

1651
00:47:04,520 --> 00:47:05,560
What did you see?

1652
00:47:05,560 --> 00:47:06,360
What happened that night?

1653
00:47:06,360 --> 00:47:07,720
Why do I have to spill everything?

1654
00:47:07,720 --> 00:47:08,640
That's all I'm saying.

1655
00:47:08,640 --> 00:47:11,080
Only the bad guys
won't spill everything.

1656
00:47:11,800 --> 00:47:12,160
Right.

1657
00:47:12,600 --> 00:47:13,560
Why?

1658
00:47:14,360 --> 00:47:15,520
You can say it now.

1659
00:47:16,560 --> 00:47:17,880
You need to be clearer.

1660
00:47:17,880 --> 00:47:18,840
You're being so vague.

1661
00:47:18,840 --> 00:47:20,720
He doesn't dare.

1662
00:47:20,720 --> 00:47:23,320
He doesn't dare frame me.

1663
00:47:23,760 --> 00:47:25,560
Come on.

1664
00:47:25,560 --> 00:47:28,520
The moment he tries
to hurt me, he panics.

1665
00:47:28,520 --> 00:47:29,280
This kid.

1666
00:47:29,280 --> 00:47:31,480
I'm so nice to him.

1667
00:47:31,480 --> 00:47:33,220
(Still keeping quiet)

1668
00:47:36,000 --> 00:47:37,360
No. 2 is so mysterious.

1669
00:47:37,360 --> 00:47:38,760
Why make it so mysterious?

1670
00:47:38,960 --> 00:47:40,040
He doesn't dare.

1671
00:47:40,360 --> 00:47:43,280
You know when a timid guy
tries to do something bad?

1672
00:47:43,280 --> 00:47:43,640
It's fine.

1673
00:47:43,640 --> 00:47:45,840
Let's hear what
the brave one has to say.

1674
00:47:46,180 --> 00:47:48,300
(Watching quietly)

