Yeah, he's not as scared anymore.

2218
01:03:53,200 --> 01:03:53,640
Yeah.

2219
01:03:53,640 --> 01:03:55,440
(Newbie player)
So it has to be scary enough

2220
01:03:55,440 --> 01:03:56,760
that even someone like me

2221
01:03:56,760 --> 01:03:58,880
can't fake being brave.

2222
01:03:59,340 --> 01:04:00,340
(Wandered into the pros)

2223
01:04:00,360 --> 01:04:02,680
Ning, you kept pretending

2224
01:04:02,680 --> 01:04:04,120
until you stopped being scared.

2225
01:04:04,120 --> 01:04:05,680
I think he has really grown.

2226
01:04:05,680 --> 01:04:06,680
That's how people are.

2227
01:04:06,680 --> 01:04:07,800
You've got to convince yourself.

2228
01:04:08,000 --> 01:04:09,560
(Ning's secret)
Tell yourself it's nothing,

2229
01:04:09,560 --> 01:04:10,760
and it becomes nothing.

2230
01:04:10,760 --> 01:04:12,480
I think I won't be scared
next time either.

2231
01:04:12,480 --> 01:04:14,120
(Try a solo mission?)
How about a solo mission?

2232
01:04:15,600 --> 01:04:17,160
I really don't think I'll be scared now,

2233
01:04:17,160 --> 01:04:18,880
because Ning just made it click for me.

2234
01:04:18,880 --> 01:04:20,680
(Daily miss Bai moment)
If Bai comes,

2235
01:04:20,680 --> 01:04:21,280
this'll be tough.

2236
01:04:21,280 --> 01:04:22,560
Seriously tough.

2237
01:04:24,000 --> 01:04:25,000
He'll dress up as a ghost
just to scare you.

2238
01:04:25,000 --> 01:04:26,200
He scares

2239
01:04:26,200 --> 01:04:27,760
even me every day.

2240
01:04:27,760 --> 01:04:30,720
I'm telling you, the moment the lights
go out or ghosts appear,

2241
01:04:30,720 --> 01:04:31,240
he gets so excited.

2242
01:04:31,240 --> 01:04:31,600
Got energized.

2243
01:04:31,600 --> 01:04:32,320
Exactly.

2244
01:04:32,320 --> 01:04:34,160
He rushes right in.

2245
01:04:36,960 --> 01:04:38,680
You probably don't watch horror movies.

2246
01:04:38,680 --> 01:04:39,800
I do.

2247
01:04:39,800 --> 01:04:40,680
You actually dare?

2248
01:04:40,680 --> 01:04:42,600
I can't watch them at all.

2249
01:04:42,600 --> 01:04:44,440
No, every kid has a rebellious phase.

2250
01:04:44,440 --> 01:04:45,520
He's that kid.

2251
01:04:45,520 --> 01:04:46,920
I watched one when I was little.

2252
01:04:46,920 --> 01:04:47,720
It scared me to death.

2253
01:04:47,720 --> 01:04:48,880
I used to have nightmares

2254
01:04:48,880 --> 01:04:51,240
about zombies chasing me.

2255
01:04:51,240 --> 01:04:51,680
Me too.

2256
01:04:51,680 --> 01:04:52,560
I had those all the time.

2257
01:04:53,200 --> 01:04:54,560
But I don't dare watch them.

2258
01:04:54,560 --> 01:04:56,120
Still, I've never had nightmares.

2259
01:04:57,240 --> 01:04:58,400
You've never had nightmares?

2260
01:04:58,400 --> 01:04:58,800
Or never had them at all?

2261
01:04:58,800 --> 01:04:59,960
I've never had nightmares.

2262
01:04:59,960 --> 01:05:02,000
From what I remember, I sleep really...

2263
01:05:02,000 --> 01:05:02,920
(Great sleep quality)
Good dreams, right?

2264
01:05:02,920 --> 01:05:03,960
I wake up

2265
01:05:04,480 --> 01:05:05,280
every morning like this.

2266
01:05:06,040 --> 01:05:07,240
Hey, just like that.

2267
01:05:07,400 --> 01:05:08,560
Every night you have good dreams.

2268
01:05:08,560 --> 01:05:09,760
That's really nice.

2269
01:05:09,860 --> 01:05:11,820
(Eat well, sleep well. Winner in life)

2270
01:05:12,280 --> 01:05:13,400
Do you still

2271
01:05:13,400 --> 01:05:15,040
like our show after filming?

2272
01:05:15,360 --> 01:05:16,480
I liked it before filming.

2273
01:05:16,480 --> 01:05:17,640
Do you still like it now?

2274
01:05:18,760 --> 01:05:19,440
I've fallen in love with it.

2275
01:05:22,880 --> 01:05:25,800
Now, do you have
an analysis of the four of us?

2276
01:05:25,800 --> 01:05:26,560
Like how we play?

2277
01:05:29,240 --> 01:05:30,920
I think whether you're good or bad,

2278
01:05:30,920 --> 01:05:32,640
you all play pretty similarly.

2279
01:05:32,840 --> 01:05:34,440
There's not much difference.

2280
01:05:34,440 --> 01:05:36,680
(Find the killer through details)
It's mostly about speech density.

2281
01:05:36,680 --> 01:05:38,600
Like last time,

2282
01:05:38,600 --> 01:05:41,320
when Ning's speech density
suddenly went up,

2283
01:05:41,320 --> 01:05:44,040
that's when he was trying hard
to prove himself.

2284
01:05:44,540 --> 01:05:45,540
(Agreed)

2285
01:05:46,360 --> 01:05:47,360
Got it all figured out already.

2286
01:05:47,360 --> 01:05:48,840
We change every season too.

2287
01:05:48,840 --> 01:05:49,360
Yeah.

2288
01:05:49,360 --> 01:05:51,320
After Season 2,

2289
01:05:51,320 --> 01:05:52,760
we felt killers would

2290
01:05:52,760 --> 01:05:54,440
deliberately stay silent

2291
01:05:54,440 --> 01:05:55,400
and avoid defending themselves.

2292
01:05:55,400 --> 01:05:55,960
That's right.

2293
01:05:55,960 --> 01:05:57,400
So in Season 3, our strategy

2294
01:05:57,400 --> 01:05:59,040
(strategy keeps upgrading)
was to defend ourselves.

2295
01:05:59,040 --> 01:06:00,680
We adjust all the time.

2296
01:06:00,680 --> 01:06:02,800
I think you definitely need to defend.

2297
01:06:02,800 --> 01:06:04,520
You need to argue logically

2298
01:06:04,520 --> 01:06:05,920
and debate others.

2299
01:06:05,920 --> 01:06:07,040
That's what makes it fun.

2300
01:06:07,040 --> 01:06:08,880
Bro, are you tired of yourself?

2301
01:06:08,880 --> 01:06:10,360
Everything starts right,

2302
01:06:10,360 --> 01:06:12,240
but the ending falls apart.

2303
01:06:12,240 --> 01:06:14,240
I didn't get everything right either.

2304
01:06:14,240 --> 01:06:16,040
But you have a certain ability:

2305
01:06:16,040 --> 01:06:16,520
like

2306
01:06:16,520 --> 01:06:17,120
I say A,

2307
01:06:17,120 --> 01:06:18,120
he says B,

2308
01:06:18,120 --> 01:06:18,800
he says C,

2309
01:06:18,800 --> 01:06:19,760
You end up

2310
01:06:19,760 --> 01:06:22,760
organizing everything for us
and still arrive at the wrong answer.

2311
01:06:24,520 --> 01:06:25,760
Yes.

2312
01:06:25,760 --> 01:06:27,720
Ning thinks more thoroughly,

2313
01:06:27,720 --> 01:06:29,880
Sometimes a bit too much.

2314
01:06:29,880 --> 01:06:31,760
Just not quite accurate in thinking.

2315
01:06:31,760 --> 01:06:33,040
So it's either slightly too much
or slightly too little.

2316
01:06:33,040 --> 01:06:34,240
It's never quite accurate.

2317
01:06:35,280 --> 01:06:35,600
Yeah.

2318
01:06:38,320 --> 01:06:39,960
Also, Ding, can you choreograph?

2319
01:06:39,960 --> 01:06:41,960
(Top-tier dance ability)
If I can dance, then I can choreograph.

2320
01:06:41,960 --> 01:06:43,760
Jin Jing has had a dream.

2321
01:06:43,760 --> 01:06:46,120
We've talked about it
for two or three years.

2322
01:06:46,120 --> 01:06:47,800
She wants us to do
a singing-and-dancing stage

2323
01:06:47,800 --> 01:06:49,440
at the Starlight Award.

2324
01:06:49,840 --> 01:06:51,440
What show is it where
we help her offstage?

2325
01:06:51,640 --> 01:06:52,480
Starlight Award.

2326
01:06:52,480 --> 01:06:53,280
(2025 Starlight Award live)
Yeah, Starlight Award.

2327
01:06:53,280 --> 01:06:54,120
Yeah, just last year.

2328
01:06:54,760 --> 01:06:55,760
You forgot it all?

2329
01:06:55,760 --> 01:06:56,960
No, I didn't forget.

2330
01:06:56,960 --> 01:06:57,640
Too many gigs.

2331
01:06:57,640 --> 01:06:58,840
Don't even know which one it was.

2332
01:06:59,240 --> 01:07:00,800
But I still remember helping you down.

2333
01:07:00,800 --> 01:07:01,960
That part was pretty good.

2334
01:07:02,340 --> 01:07:03,300
(Very observant)

2335
01:07:03,360 --> 01:07:04,680
You made Xu Zhisheng pretty awkward.

2336
01:07:05,560 --> 01:07:06,120
Xu Zhisheng?

2337
01:07:06,360 --> 01:07:07,440
He came to help you, right?

2338
01:07:07,440 --> 01:07:08,480
Yeah, he was about to.

2339
01:07:11,040 --> 01:07:11,520
After I debuted,

2340
01:07:11,520 --> 01:07:12,320
I met Ding

2341
01:07:12,320 --> 01:07:13,640
more often.

2342
01:07:13,640 --> 01:07:14,320
Because we're

2343
01:07:14,320 --> 01:07:15,440
(Music-related stuff)
both in music.

2344
01:07:16,080 --> 01:07:16,840
So this show

2345
01:07:16,840 --> 01:07:17,960
counts as a crossover show.

2346
01:07:18,260 --> 01:07:20,100
(How so?)

2347
01:07:20,400 --> 01:07:21,240
It lets someone like me,

2348
01:07:21,240 --> 01:07:22,280
who knows nothing about music

2349
01:07:22,280 --> 01:07:23,760
end up meeting two people
from the music field.

2350
01:07:24,680 --> 01:07:25,760
You really don't know anything at all?

2351
01:07:25,760 --> 01:07:28,040
(Online consultation)
Ning, can you fix him?

2352
01:07:28,720 --> 01:07:29,600
So I'm telling you,

2353
01:07:29,600 --> 01:07:30,720
when you're born,

2354
01:07:30,960 --> 01:07:32,920
(#Ning's life lesson)
Life gives you

2355
01:07:32,920 --> 01:07:34,000
certain attribute points.

2356
01:07:34,560 --> 01:07:35,960
Some get music talent,

2357
01:07:35,960 --> 01:07:37,240
some get acting talent,

2358
01:07:37,240 --> 01:07:38,320
some get dance talent.

2359
01:07:39,600 --> 01:07:41,920
Your skill points are limited.

2360
01:07:41,920 --> 01:07:43,120
Yeah, fixed amount.

2361
01:07:43,120 --> 01:07:45,240
So why are you all-round?

2362
01:07:45,240 --> 01:07:46,840
I'm all-round in the sense that

2363
01:07:46,840 --> 01:07:49,000
(Humble, bro)
I'm kind of average at everything.

2364
01:07:51,760 --> 01:07:52,720
When I tried recording the theme song,

2365
01:07:52,720 --> 01:07:53,840
I couldn't even hit a single note.

2366
01:07:55,280 --> 01:07:56,480
It's too high.

2367
01:07:56,480 --> 01:07:58,240
What's your comfortable range?

2368
01:07:58,240 --> 01:07:59,570
Middle voice.

2369
01:07:59,580 --> 01:08:01,920
♪Praise builds this hall♪

2370
01:08:02,080 --> 01:08:03,440
Your comfortable range is

2371
01:08:03,440 --> 01:08:04,200
mid to low.

2372
01:08:04,200 --> 01:08:06,200
♪Sunset crosses the sea
beyond the mountains♪

2373
01:08:06,520 --> 01:08:07,760
Why didn't you ask me?

2374
01:08:07,760 --> 01:08:09,800
Yes, let's ask
what his comfortable vocal range is.

2375
01:08:09,800 --> 01:08:11,120
I think it's a moo tone

2376
01:08:11,220 --> 01:08:12,780
(Sister knows brother best)

2377
01:08:13,200 --> 01:08:15,520
♪Such a painful realization♪

2378
01:08:16,520 --> 01:08:18,640
Today we fixed these five bugs.

2379
01:08:18,640 --> 01:08:19,880
What impact will it have

2380
01:08:19,880 --> 01:08:21,430
for the later dungeons?

2381
01:08:23,390 --> 01:08:24,350
Didn't we say before?

2382
01:08:24,350 --> 01:08:25,640
He Jiahuan

2383
01:08:25,640 --> 01:08:26,430
has no fear,

2384
01:08:26,430 --> 01:08:27,000
no restraints.

2385
01:08:27,000 --> 01:08:27,920
Something like that.

2386
01:08:27,920 --> 01:08:28,720
But it seems like

2387
01:08:28,720 --> 01:08:30,310
is it actually the opposite

2388
01:08:30,310 --> 01:08:31,080
of what we experienced.

2389
01:08:31,270 --> 01:08:32,600
(Experience opposite to the description)
It's all the opposite.

2390
01:08:33,040 --> 01:08:35,040
(Enter Door of Truth to join us)
We have the best gaming teammates.

2391
01:08:35,040 --> 01:08:37,040
There is no fear and no restraints here.

2392
01:08:37,040 --> 01:08:38,470
We are all restraints

2393
01:08:38,470 --> 01:08:39,350
and also fear.

2394
01:08:39,350 --> 01:08:41,200
But it seems like

2395
01:08:41,200 --> 01:08:42,000
it was modified.

2396
01:08:42,840 --> 01:08:43,760
So after we fix it,

2397
01:08:43,760 --> 01:08:44,960
will it become the same again?

2398
01:08:44,960 --> 01:08:47,040
It's possible those stories were...

2399
01:08:47,310 --> 01:08:48,600
They were caused by the five bugs

2400
01:08:48,600 --> 01:08:49,270
we just fixed.

2401
01:08:49,270 --> 01:08:50,240
Five bugs.

2402
01:08:50,240 --> 01:08:50,920
Yeah.

2403
01:08:53,800 --> 01:08:54,960
Was Bai Design

2404
01:08:54,960 --> 01:08:56,840
(Star employee: Designer Bai)
designed by Designer Bai?

2405
01:08:56,840 --> 01:08:57,920
Because he

2406
01:08:57,920 --> 01:08:59,080
designed the whole game.

2407
01:08:59,080 --> 01:08:59,680
Yes.

2408
01:08:59,680 --> 01:09:01,270
So does that mean

2409
01:09:01,270 --> 01:09:02,200
what we experienced

2410
01:09:02,200 --> 01:09:03,640
is completely opposite

2411
01:09:03,640 --> 01:09:04,840
to the story's official description?

2412
01:09:04,840 --> 01:09:05,640
That's possible.

2413
01:09:05,840 --> 01:09:08,200
(Cross-instance rating)
An family not only perfects products,

2414
01:09:08,200 --> 01:09:10,430
but also sincerely shares this goodness

2415
01:09:10,430 --> 01:09:11,640
with every consumer.

2416
01:09:11,640 --> 01:09:13,880
Every child is seen while growing up.

2417
01:09:13,880 --> 01:09:16,240
This part of life is completely

2418
01:09:16,240 --> 01:09:18,560
the opposite of everything
I've experienced.

2419
01:09:18,560 --> 01:09:20,840
(Starlight Cafe)
You use a 9.9-yuan

2420
01:09:20,840 --> 01:09:22,760
coffee as a medium,

2421
01:09:22,760 --> 01:09:24,120
but what you're really promoting

2422
01:09:24,120 --> 01:09:26,120
is practical AI anti-scam technology.

2423
01:09:26,120 --> 01:09:28,000
It's a completely different story

2424
01:09:28,000 --> 01:09:29,880
from what we experienced.

2425
01:09:29,880 --> 01:09:30,720
It also means

2426
01:09:30,720 --> 01:09:32,520
the game world

2427
01:09:32,520 --> 01:09:33,600
has been tampered with.

2428
01:09:33,600 --> 01:09:34,200
Yeah.

2429
01:09:34,470 --> 01:09:36,120
Could someone have kidnapped him

2430
01:09:36,120 --> 01:09:37,560
and altered his memories?

2431
01:09:37,580 --> 01:09:40,620
(Someone kidnapped Designer Bai)

2432
01:09:40,640 --> 01:09:42,270
Could our final mission be

2433
01:09:42,270 --> 01:09:44,310
to rescue him?

2434
01:09:44,720 --> 01:09:45,920
What if one of the five of us

2435
01:09:45,920 --> 01:09:47,240
is actually him?

2436
01:09:47,300 --> 01:09:50,460
(Designer Bai is one of them)

2437
01:09:50,470 --> 01:09:51,470
That's me.

2438
01:09:52,080 --> 01:09:53,430
Well, anything's possible.

2439
01:09:53,430 --> 01:09:53,760
Yeah.

2440
01:09:53,760 --> 01:09:54,480
That's right.

2441
01:09:55,200 --> 01:09:56,160
So, what are you looking forward to

2442
01:09:56,160 --> 01:09:57,200
Ghost Stories of Tui City?

2443
01:09:57,200 --> 01:09:59,120
I hope our relationships later on

2444
01:09:59,120 --> 01:10:00,480
get even more dramatic.

2445
01:10:00,880 --> 01:10:01,800
You're hooked already.

2446
01:10:01,800 --> 01:10:02,960
It's still not dramatic enough?

2447
01:10:02,960 --> 01:10:04,760
Everything you
can't experience in real life,

2448
01:10:04,760 --> 01:10:06,600
you want to experience here?

2449
01:10:07,160 --> 01:10:08,160
(Hit the nail on the head)
Exactly.

2450
01:10:08,160 --> 01:10:08,880
The more it shows

2451
01:10:08,880 --> 01:10:10,440
relationships you
don't see in real life,

2452
01:10:10,440 --> 01:10:11,400
the more it happens here,

2453
01:10:11,400 --> 01:10:11,960
the more people love it.

2454
01:10:12,280 --> 01:10:14,320
What kind of relationships
don't exist in real life?

2455
01:10:14,320 --> 01:10:15,320
Give me an example.

2456
01:10:15,320 --> 01:10:17,080
In real life you'd never run into

2457
01:10:17,080 --> 01:10:18,440
a brother–sister kind of storyline.

2458
01:10:18,440 --> 01:10:20,000
Like that all lovers end up
as siblings trope.

2459
01:10:20,000 --> 01:10:21,840
(Has him figured out)
He's just chasing that rush.

2460
01:10:21,840 --> 01:10:23,640
Zhang Linghe enjoyed himself.

2461
01:10:23,640 --> 01:10:24,760
He loved every second.

2462
01:10:24,760 --> 01:10:25,600
It's not just that.

2463
01:10:25,600 --> 01:10:27,600
It's because he was the son.

2464
01:10:27,600 --> 01:10:29,280
He was my son last season.

2465
01:10:29,280 --> 01:10:30,960
Now he's yours this season.

2466
01:10:30,960 --> 01:10:32,280
He wants a promotion.

2467
01:10:32,280 --> 01:10:34,240
He wants to be a father.

2468
01:10:34,240 --> 01:10:35,480
I can do it too.

2469
01:10:35,480 --> 01:10:36,460
(Same dream)

2470
01:10:36,640 --> 01:10:37,440
In terms of seniority?

2471
01:10:37,440 --> 01:10:37,760
Yes.

2472
01:10:37,760 --> 01:10:40,000
Okay. Ding and Zhang Linghe
has the same request.

2473
01:10:40,060 --> 01:10:41,080
(Applying for "ultimate seniority")
Wouldn't that

2474
01:10:41,080 --> 01:10:41,920
throw you out of character?

2475
01:10:41,920 --> 01:10:42,920
Are you sure?

2476
01:10:42,920 --> 01:10:44,400
It won't. I'll be the senior.

2477
01:10:45,640 --> 01:10:47,720
My little senior. My gosh.

2478
01:10:48,800 --> 01:10:49,800
My little senior.

2479
01:10:49,800 --> 01:10:51,240
That's what we'll call you.

2480
01:10:52,560 --> 01:10:54,280
I hope it gets even scarier.

2481
01:10:54,280 --> 01:10:55,320
You're not scared.

2482
01:10:55,320 --> 01:10:56,480
I just hope

2483
01:10:56,480 --> 01:10:57,840
when you're targeting the new players,

2484
01:10:57,840 --> 01:10:59,200
(Certain "new" players)
you'll remember someone

2485
01:10:59,200 --> 01:11:01,360
is also scared of these things.

2486
01:11:01,360 --> 01:11:03,240
No. I wasn't targeting him.

2487
01:11:03,240 --> 01:11:04,760
I just thought it was fun.

2488
01:11:04,960 --> 01:11:05,920
Yeah. Super fun.

2489
01:11:08,240 --> 01:11:09,760
